org.devgateway.ocds.persistence.mongo

Class Location<T extends org.springframework.data.mongodb.core.geo.GeoJson<?>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.devgateway.ocds.persistence.mongo.Location<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Identifiable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultLocation

    public abstract class Location<T extends org.springframework.data.mongodb.core.geo.GeoJson<?>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Identifiable
    Location

    The location where activity related to this tender, contract or license will be delivered, or will take place. A location can be described by either a geometry (point location, line or polygon), or a gazetteer entry, or both.

      • getGeometry

        public abstract T getGeometry()
        We follow the [GeoJSON standard](http://geojson.org/) to express basic location information, using latitude and longitude values in the [WGS84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System) (EPSG:4326) projection. A point location can be identified by geocoding a delivery address. For concession licenses, or other contracts covering a polygon location which is not contained in a known gazetteer, polygon and multi-polygon can be used.
        Returns:
        The geometry
